Sosana</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#f7f5e6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvonic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vonic</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>4/16/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333399>8:12:36 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: . . .</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Some other items of note that are stated elsewhere but bear repeating when you do the final stage of this quest.  <br>
1.  Make sure Fergul is up and no one is camping the fort when you hand in your harness - if hes dead, no leggings.<br>
<br>
2.  Make sure you annouce to the zone your starting the quest - may or may not prevent inadvertant interference.<br>
<br>
3.  Make sure you have enough fire power to take Fergul out quickly - for 2 reasons.  1 - if he gets to the EW zone area, he'll poof on ya. 2 - you may run into some less than stellar individuals that will deliberately try and KS Fergul.<br>
<br>
4.  Be aware that the Broodmother will be charmed and will come after you - get your business done and get out of her way.<br>
<br>
These are the main complications to the way the final step in this quest works.  Plan for them and you should be successful.  Good luck.<br>
<br>
Vonic<br>
<br>
55th Preserver<br>
